        "hook_text": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Be honest — when was the last time your bag made someone stop and ask: <em>\"Where did you get that?\"</em></p><p>Not a Rs. 15,000 designer knockoff. Not a plain black tote from a mall. Not another synthetic bag that started peeling after two months of Mumbai rains.</p><p>When a close friend came home last Diwali, she wasn't carrying a Zara or a Charles & Keith. She had this <strong>small, round, striped bag</strong> — and it had a quiet confidence that her entire outfit borrowed from.</p><p>\"What's that?\" I had to ask.</p><p><em>\"Nova Everyday Clutch. Gets me stopped everywhere I go. And it costs less than your auto rides in a month.\"</em></p>",
            "text_size": 17,
            "text_color": "#2d2d2d",
            "highlighted_text_color": "#000000",
            "highlighted_text_background": "#fcc947",
            "accent_text_color": "#f44336",
            "accent_text_background": "#fff5f5",
            "top_padding": 20,
            "bottom_padding": 8
          }
        },
        "problem_agitation": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<h3>Here's the real problem with most bags under Rs. 2,000</h3><p>We've all been there. You find a bag that looks good in the photo. You order it. It arrives — and in person, it feels cheap. The stitching is uneven. The clasp is flimsy. After three months, the lining starts to tear.</p><p>And if you go the other route — spending Rs. 5,000 to Rs. 10,000 — you're either overpaying for a logo or getting something so safe and boring it disappears into your outfit.</p><p><em>\"Most bags are either too cheap to last or too expensive to feel worth it. There's a gap in the middle — and Nova fills it perfectly.\"</em></p><p>The Indian bag market has never had a product that offered <strong>handcrafted quality + a distinctive silhouette + an accessible price point</strong> — until now.</p>",
            "text_size": 17,
            "text_color": "#2d2d2d",
            "highlighted_text_color": "#000000",
            "highlighted_text_background": "#fcc947",
            "accent_text_color": "#f44336",
